description:
From the small town of Shrewsbury, England comes Blame Bilston. A  trio of young men who love fuzzy guitars and working class songs in the vein of Nirvana and Alice In Chains. The bands latest release, Yesterday again, is their Critical Mass Music debut and is equally as impressive as anything Kurt and Layne ever put out. Give em a shot, I think you'll like what you hear.

name: The Panic Beats - "You're Next"
description:
The brainchild of Dale VanThomme, The Panic Beats hail from Port Huron, MI and play in your face, horror inducing punk rock. The bands latest release, "You're Next", is an Infested Records debut that's sure to get your attention. From the monster riffs and maniac influenced songs right down to the artwork. This is a must have CD for anyone into scary movies and slaughterhouse style punk rock.

description:
Toronto Canada's own Fairmounts bring their own style of pop punk to the masses with their debut full length! Big harmonies and lots of sing along songs about girls, booze and The Fugitive! Joe Queer even makes an appearance on the track "6 Outta 10". And the CD was mastered by Stephen Egerton from Descendents. A TRUE classic in the making!
